A lecturer at the Department of Technical Education, Hassan Usman Polytechnic Katsina, Dr. Bello Birchi, has been kidnapped. Birchi was whisked away at his country home, at about midnight yesterday at Tashar Bara’u village along Dutsinma road in Katsina state. The chairman of Academic Staff Union of the Polytechnic (ASUP), Dr Sabi’u Yau Abdullahi, who confirmed the development said the union is greatly disturbed over the unfortunate incidence. “No communication so far has been made with the abductors.” he added.  Details later… Re: No money to pay poly lecturers, FG says Katsina poly rector gets ultimatum on fraud allegation Dispute with poly lecturers to be resolved soon — Wike Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin